threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit LSB executable, Renesas SH, version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, not stripped

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This ELF binary is a DDoS botnet agent, likely a variant of Mirai or Gafgyt, compiled for the RISC-V architecture (rv32gc). It contains numerous modular attack functions designed to launch distributed denial-of-service attacks, including SendOVH, Send100UP, SendNUKE, SendPAKI, SendZAP, and SendHTTP. It includes features for spoofing User-Agents, manipulating system watchdogs (/dev/watchdog) to prevent reboots, and a command-and-control (C2) processing engine (processCmd). Relevant IOCs include the presence of numerous DDoS-related function names and hardcoded User-Agent strings used for HTTP flood attacks.
